<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>In _loggerSanity(), if Zend_Cache_Core is initialised before autoloading has been turned on, a missing require_once statement for Zend_Log causes:</p>

<p>Fatal error: Class 'Zend_Log' not found in /path/to/library/Zend/Cache/Core.php on line 717</p>

<p>(as at revision 21293).</p>

<p>Can be easily worked around by autoloading earlier, requiring Zend_Log yourself or turning off logging, but probably should be fixed nonetheless.</p>

